<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1451501-which-place-and-period-is-the-story-set">Which place and period is the story set? Do i have to know anything about the background of the country&#39;s situation during the time when story is set to understand the events better?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1451501'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F16532.Of_Love_and_Shadows">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1451501-which-place-and-period-is-the-story-set">2 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1451501-which-place-and-period-is-the-story-set">See all 3 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/86766160-anne"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/86766160-anne">Anne</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">No, you really don&apos;t need to know anything about the country. Allende never names the country, but we can assume it is her native Chile, since her hus<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">No, you really don't need to know anything about the country. Allende never names the country, but we can assume it is her native Chile, since her husband was the president of Chile and was murdered in a military coup. The events in the book are what happens to the characters. There's nothing implied.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

