<span id="freeTextContainer1561204312122067444">A satisfying tale of love and political commitment. This is Allendes&apos;s second novel and it is written in the same lilting style as the first. <br/><br/>There is Irene Beltran, the unconventional daughter of a wealthy family, and Francisco Leal, son of Spanish exiles. She is the journalist and he is the photographer. They both work hard to uncover misdeeds of the political government.<br/><br/>Then there is Evangelina Ranquileo, a strange farmgirl near the village of Los Riscos who seems to possess supernatural powe</span>
  <span id="freeText1561204312122067444" style="display:none">A satisfying tale of love and political commitment. This is Allendes's second novel and it is written in the same lilting style as the first. <br /><br />There is Irene Beltran, the unconventional daughter of a wealthy family, and Francisco Leal, son of Spanish exiles. She is the journalist and he is the photographer. They both work hard to uncover misdeeds of the political government.<br /><br />Then there is Evangelina Ranquileo, a strange farmgirl near the village of Los Riscos who seems to possess supernatural powers.<br /><br />I loved, loved, loved this book. Very worthy of Allende's extraordinary literary talents.<br /><br />5 stars</span>
